balanceOf(address).details: In non-live state, only ContractAddresses.VAULT has balance of 1.

constructor.details: Mints token #0 (eternal trophy) to ContractAddresses.VAULT immediately.      All dependencies are fixed at deploy time.

placeAsk(uint256,uint256,uint40).details: Burns ASK_FEE (10 BURNIE). Caller must own the token.      Listing is cleared on any transfer of the token.

processDormant(uint32).details: Intentionally out-of-spec (events without state changes); advances an internal cursor so callers can      process the range over multiple transactions.

processPendingMints(uint32,uint32,uint25.details: Called by the game contract; rotates through the queue using a VRF-provided offset for this airdrop.

purchase((uint256,uint8,uint8,bool,bytes.details: Main entry point for all purchases. Routes to _purchase or _mintAndBurn.      SECURITY: Blocked when RNG is locked.

params.params: Purchase parameters (quantity, kind, payKind, payInCoin, affiliateCode).

purchaseMapForAffiliate(address,uint256).details: Access: affiliate program only. Bypasses payments, just enqueues maps.      Used when affiliates redeem accumulated rewards for maps.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Token #0 is special (eternal trophy). All other tokens get traits.      Reverts for nonexistent or burned tokens.

totalSupply().details: Returns minted - burned. In non-live state, only token #0 exists.

acceptOffer(uint256,address,uint216).notice: Accept a specific offer by supplying the bidder/amount you observed off-chain (e.g., via `bestOffer`).

advanceBase().notice: Retire all tokens below `newBaseTokenId` (except token 0) at level transition.

balanceOf(address).notice: Get token balance of an address.

bestOffer(uint256).notice: Return the highest active offer (funded + unexpired) for a token, if any.

burnFromGame(address,uint256[]).notice: Burn a batch of player tokens

cancelOffer(uint256).notice: Cancel an active on-chain offer for a tokenId (no refund).

nextTokenId().notice: Get the next token ID that will be minted.

placeAsk(uint256,uint256,uint40).notice: Place an on-chain ask (listing) for a token.

placeOffer(uint256,uint216,uint40).notice: Place an on-chain offer for a tokenId; burns the flat posting fee.

processDormant(uint32).notice: Emits burn Transfer events for the most-recently-retired level range to help indexers catch up.

processPendingMints(uint32,uint32,uint25.notice: Batch-mint queued purchases, respecting an airdrop cap and optional multiplier for reward mints.

queueRewardMints(address,uint32).notice: Queue reward mints without applying purchase bonuses.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Check if contract supports an interface.

tokensOwed(address).notice: Pending owed mints for a player (used by processPendingMints).
